decision_conditions:
1. This application for a non-material amendment to planning permission P090206 has been made under section 96A of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990. The effect of the proposed changes to the front and rear elevations of 39-51 Wharfdale Road are considered to be non-material to the overall appearance of the approved development. The minor non-material amendments comprise of:

Front Elevation
- the original brick cornice/parapet at nos. 47, 49 & 51 Wharfdale Road to be repaired and retained;
- the profiled sand and cement cornice/parapet at nos. 39, 41 & 43 Wharfdale Road is to be reinstated to match the existing at no. 45;
- the cornice line above the ground floor windows and entrance door is to remain in its existing condition (i.e. a staggered break between nos. 45 & 47);
- a 35mm recessed render panel with a stone sub cill below is to be provided to the basement lightwell areas below the entrance doors/bridge link;
- the dormer windows at third floor level are to be narrowed;
- glazing bars are to be provided in the arched fanlight window above the entrance doors;
- 3 no. cast iron rainwater pipes with traditional cast iron hoppers to the head are to be provided.

Rear elevation
- the cill heights and window sizes at first and second floor levels are to be reduced in order to accommodate bathrooms and kitchens 
- traditional timber painted French doors with a splayed brick header detail above to match the windows are to be provided in place of sliding patio doors 
- French windows are also to be provided in the basement lightwell;
- rainwater goods and hopper details are to be provided;
- smoke extract Velux windows are to be provided to the flat roof at the head of each stairwell;
- 3 no. roof lights are to be omitted from the upper section of the roof;
- the dormer windows at third floor level are to be narrowed;
- two window openings to the right-hand ground and basement levels are to be in-filled and a secondary party wall is to be provided 1m from the existing at ground and basement level; 
- Extended painted timber cills are to be provided for the sash window unit in place of reconstituted stone window cills.

For clarity, no other changes have been agreed with the Local Planning Authority under this application.
